%% Game Development Decision Flowchart
%% Genre to Platform to Engine/Language

flowchart TD
    START[I want to make a game] --> GENRE{What genre?}

    GENRE -->|Strategy / RTS| S1{Scale?}
    S1 -->|Small-mid| S2[Godot 4]
    S1 -->|Massive sim| S3[Custom C++ or Rust]

    GENRE -->|Retro FPS| R1{Authenticity?}
    R1 -->|Maximum retro| R2[Custom Rust+wgpu or C++]
    R1 -->|Retro aesthetic| R3[Godot 4 + retro shaders]

    GENRE -->|Mobile casual| M1[Unity or Godot 4]

    GENRE -->|Browser game| W1{2D or 3D?}
    W1 -->|2D| W2[Phaser 3]
    W1 -->|3D| W3[Three.js or Babylon.js]

    GENRE -->|3D game| T1{Scope?}
    T1 -->|AAA| T2[Unreal Engine 5]
    T1 -->|Indie| T3[Godot 4]
    T1 -->|Custom tech| T4[Bevy or Custom Rust]

    GENRE -->|Card / Board / UI| C1[Godot 4 or Tauri + web]

    GENRE -->|Voxel / Simulation| V1[Custom Rust or C++]

    GENRE -->|2D Platformer| P1[Godot 4]
